class Solution {
    public int largestPerimeter(int[] nums) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        for(int i=nums.length-1;i>=2;i--){
            if(nums[i-2]+nums[i-1]>nums[i]) return nums[i-2]+nums[i-1]+nums[i];
        }
        return 0;
    }
}

Note: For 3 sides a, b, c (sorted):

A triangle is valid only 
a+b>c

(Where c is the largest side)

If this condition fails → not a triangle 
